1.What is a Gitrepository?
  A Git repository is the .git/ folder inside a project. This repository tracks all changes made to files in your project, 
  building a history over time. Meaning, if you delete the .git/ folder, then you delete your projectâ€™s history.
2.What are the 2 special features of a Gitrepository?
  Feature Branch Workflow. One of the biggest advantages of Git is its branching capabilities.
  Distributed Development. Each developer gets a working copy that points back to a single central repository.
3.Why or how do those features help your collaborative project?
  It helps to keep things organized and not all over the place. It can also be easily accesible to the whole group whenever they need it, 
  wherever they are.
